title: How has the proportion of category A calls attended within 19 minutes changed?
analysis_commentary: For the completed financial years 2011/12 and 2012/13, the service managed to successfully meet the 95% target. Between 2010/11 and 2011/12, there was a slight decrease in the proportion of category A calls being responded to within 19 minutes; from 96.8% to 96.0%. There was one month (within the most recent 28 months) where the 95% target was not met (December 2012), with 94.6% of calls being responded to within 19 minutes. This is attributable to a single trust failing to reach the standard.
data_source: NHS England, Ambulance Quality Indicators: System Indicators
